## ğŸ› ï¸ Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Frontend | React, Vite, TypeScript | Responsive portfolio UI |
| Hosting | Amazon S3 | Static asset storage |
| CDN | Amazon CloudFront | Global low-latency delivery |
| Security | ACM + OAC | HTTPS + S3 origin protection |
| API | AWS API Gateway | Serverless REST endpoint |
| Backend | AWS Lambda (Python) | Visitor counter logic |
| Database | Amazon DynamoDB | Visitor count persistence |
| IaC | Terraform | All infrastructure as code |
| CI/CD | GitHub Actions | Automated build & deploy |

---

## âœ¨ Key Features

**Serverless Architecture**
Zero server management â€” Lambda scales automatically with demand and costs nothing when idle.

**Infrastructure as Code**
Every AWS resource (S3, CloudFront, Lambda, DynamoDB, ACM, API Gateway) is defined and versioned in Terraform â€” fully reproducible and auditable.

**Secure by Default**
- HTTPS enforced via AWS Certificate Manager
- S3 bucket is completely private â€” only accessible through CloudFront via Origin Access Control (OAC)
- No public S3 URLs exposed

**Automated CI/CD Pipeline**
Every push to `main` triggers a GitHub Actions workflow that builds, tests, and deploys â€” with zero manual steps.

**Live Visitor Counter**
A real-time serverless visitor counter backed by DynamoDB demonstrates end-to-end cloud integration.

